00:23:44.150 --> 00:23:49.150
that Jesus dignified people in the way he communicated with them.

00:23:49.150 --> 00:23:53.150
He often asked meaningful questions

00:23:53.150 --> 00:23:58.150
and listened attentively to the answers

00:23:58.150 --> 00:24:02.150
before he shared his gift.

00:24:02.150 --> 00:24:04.150
For a few minutes this morning,

00:24:04.150 --> 00:24:09.150
let's consider two occasions when Jesus did just that.

00:24:09.150 --> 00:24:13.150
In doing so, we'll get some pointers

00:24:13.150 --> 00:24:17.150
that will assist you to be effective

00:24:17.150 --> 00:24:21.150
in sharing your gift of Gilead training.

00:24:21.150 --> 00:24:25.150
The first account is found in the Bible book of Mark, chapter 10.

00:24:25.150 --> 00:24:27.150
Let's turn there to gather.

00:24:27.150 --> 00:24:31.150
Mark, chapter 10, beginning in verse 35.

00:24:31.150 --> 00:24:37.359
James and John, the sons of Zebedee,

00:24:37.359 --> 00:24:39.359
approached him and said to him,

00:24:39.359 --> 00:24:46.359
teacher, we want you to do for us whatever we ask of you.

00:24:46.359 --> 00:24:49.359
He said to them,

00:24:49.359 --> 00:24:53.359
what do you want me to do for you?

00:24:53.359 --> 00:24:55.359
They replied,

00:24:55.359 --> 00:24:58.359
grant us to sit down one at your right hand

00:24:58.359 --> 00:25:03.309
and one at your left in your glory.

00:25:03.309 --> 00:25:06.309
The parallel account in Matthew

00:25:06.309 --> 00:25:10.309
reveals that James and John did not approach Jesus

00:25:10.309 --> 00:25:12.309
on their own.

00:25:12.309 --> 00:25:16.309
They had their mother do it for them.

00:25:16.309 --> 00:25:21.309
Do you think as this woman approached Jesus,

00:25:21.309 --> 00:25:25.309
he knew what she wanted?

00:25:25.309 --> 00:25:27.309
Probably.

00:25:27.309 --> 00:25:30.309
How did he deal with her?

00:25:30.309 --> 00:25:32.309
Did he interrupt her?

00:25:32.309 --> 00:25:34.309
Reprimand her?

00:25:34.309 --> 00:25:35.309
No.

00:25:35.309 --> 00:25:39.309
Instead he asked a question.

00:25:39.309 --> 00:25:42.309
What do you want me to do for you?

00:25:42.309 --> 00:25:47.750
The second account is just a few verses down.

00:25:47.750 --> 00:25:52.750
Mark, chapter 10, beginning in verse 46.

00:25:52.750 --> 00:25:57.750
Here we learn about a blind beggar named Bartimaeus.

00:25:57.750 --> 00:25:59.750
He sat by the road,

00:25:59.750 --> 00:26:03.750
and when he heard that Jesus was passing by, he called out.

00:26:03.750 --> 00:26:08.750
Son of David, Jesus, have mercy on me.

00:26:08.750 --> 00:26:11.750
The crowd tried to quiet him,

00:26:11.750 --> 00:26:15.750
but Bartimaeus called out even more loudly.

00:26:15.750 --> 00:26:18.750
Jesus stopped and said,

00:26:18.750 --> 00:26:22.509
bring him to me.

00:26:22.509 --> 00:26:27.509
Now Bartimaeus had an audience with the Son of God.

00:26:27.509 --> 00:26:32.890
How did Jesus address Bartimaeus?

00:26:32.890 --> 00:26:34.890
In verse 51,

00:26:34.890 --> 00:26:36.890
Jesus said to him,

00:26:36.890 --> 00:26:41.890
what do you want me to do for you?

00:26:41.890 --> 00:26:43.890
The blind man said to him,

00:26:43.890 --> 00:26:45.890
rebony,

00:26:45.890 --> 00:26:48.890
let me recover my sight.

00:26:48.890 --> 00:26:50.890
And Jesus said to him,

00:26:50.890 --> 00:26:54.890
go, your faith has made you well.

00:26:54.890 --> 00:26:57.890
And immediately he recovered his sight

00:26:57.890 --> 00:27:03.460
and he began to follow Jesus on the road.

00:27:03.460 --> 00:27:07.460
What do you want me to do for you?

00:27:07.460 --> 00:27:12.460
The same question in both accounts, very different situations.

00:27:12.460 --> 00:27:18.990
Why do you think Jesus asked this question?

00:27:18.990 --> 00:27:23.990
Well, he accomplished at least four things.

00:27:23.990 --> 00:27:25.990
What were they?

00:27:25.990 --> 00:27:27.990
Well, first of all,

00:27:27.990 --> 00:27:29.990
he dignified his audience

00:27:29.990 --> 00:27:35.849
by encouraging communication.

00:27:35.849 --> 00:27:37.849
Number two,

00:27:37.849 --> 00:27:44.849
he allowed his audience to reveal what was in his or her heart,

00:27:44.849 --> 00:27:50.819
to put it on the table as it were.

00:27:50.819 --> 00:27:52.819
In his dealings with James and John,

00:27:52.819 --> 00:27:57.819
the question actually protected Jesus

00:27:57.819 --> 00:28:02.819
and gave him an opportunity to give those two apostles

00:28:02.819 --> 00:28:06.819
a valuable lesson in modesty.

00:28:06.819 --> 00:28:09.819
This matter of giving the right and left places in the kingdom

00:28:09.819 --> 00:28:11.819
is not mine to give.

00:28:11.819 --> 00:28:17.519
Finally, in the case of Bartimaeus,

00:28:17.519 --> 00:28:21.519
would you agree the question provided opportunity

00:28:21.519 --> 00:28:24.519
to strengthen Bartimaeus' faith

00:28:24.519 --> 00:28:28.519
and to give him effective assistance?

00:28:28.519 --> 00:28:32.519
Allowing Bartimaeus to articulate his desire,

00:28:32.519 --> 00:28:35.519
what do you want?

00:28:35.519 --> 00:28:39.519
And then to experience the immediate realization

00:28:39.519 --> 00:28:42.519
would have left no doubt in Bartimaeus' mind

00:28:42.519 --> 00:28:44.519
that he had been considered.

00:28:44.519 --> 00:28:46.519
And how did it affect him?

00:28:46.519 --> 00:28:53.519
Well, the account says he began to follow Jesus on the road.

00:28:53.519 --> 00:28:58.519
It's a beautiful example of asking a question

00:28:58.519 --> 00:29:03.519
that helps you to share your gift.

00:29:03.519 --> 00:29:08.089
When I was a newly appointed circuit overseer,

00:29:08.089 --> 00:29:11.089
the elders in a congregation that I was serving

00:29:11.089 --> 00:29:16.089
expressed concern about a sister who was missing meetings.

00:29:16.089 --> 00:29:19.089
They asked me if I would be willing to make a shepherding visit.

00:29:19.089 --> 00:29:22.089
Of course, I was happy to do that.

00:29:22.089 --> 00:29:24.089
The arrangements were made,

00:29:24.089 --> 00:29:27.089
another elder accompanied me,

00:29:27.089 --> 00:29:31.089
and I shared all of the appropriate verses

00:29:31.089 --> 00:29:34.089
about meeting attendants.

00:29:34.089 --> 00:29:36.089
The sister listened,

00:29:36.089 --> 00:29:38.089
and as we were leaving,

00:29:38.089 --> 00:29:40.089
she looked me in the eye,

00:29:40.089 --> 00:29:42.089
and she said,

00:29:42.089 --> 00:29:45.559
you don't have a clue.

00:29:45.559 --> 00:29:49.559
At the time, I thought she was being disrespectful.

00:29:49.559 --> 00:29:52.559
But as I thought about it,

00:29:52.559 --> 00:29:55.559
I came to wish that instead of showing up

00:29:55.559 --> 00:29:58.559
with all the appropriate verses,

00:29:58.559 --> 00:30:03.559
I had showed up with all of the appropriate questions.

00:30:03.559 --> 00:30:07.559
What do you want me to do for you?

00:30:07.559 --> 00:30:09.559
How may I help?

00:30:09.559 --> 00:30:13.559
What's been happening in your life?

00:30:13.559 --> 00:30:17.559
Those kinds of questions allow you

00:30:17.559 --> 00:30:21.559
to render meaningful assistance.

00:30:21.559 --> 00:30:24.559
I learned from that experience.

00:30:24.559 --> 00:30:27.559
I hope you can learn from my mistake.

00:30:27.559 --> 00:30:30.559
Don't make the mistake of thinking you know

00:30:30.559 --> 00:30:33.559
what a person wants or needs.

00:30:33.559 --> 00:30:35.559
Jesus did know,

00:30:35.559 --> 00:30:41.420
and he still asked questions.

00:30:41.420 --> 00:30:45.859
Didn't I find the audience?

00:30:45.859 --> 00:30:50.859
Allow your listener to reveal what is in his or her heart.

00:30:50.859 --> 00:30:53.859
It may protect you,

00:30:53.859 --> 00:30:57.859
and it allows you to render meaningful assistance.

00:30:57.859 --> 00:31:02.859
Approach your assignment the way Jesus approached his.

00:31:03.859 --> 00:31:06.859
What do you want me to do for you?

00:31:06.859 --> 00:31:08.859
If you do,

00:31:08.859 --> 00:31:12.859
not only will you effectively share your gift,

00:31:12.859 --> 00:31:18.839
you will be a gift wherever you serve.

00:31:18.839 --> 00:31:20.839
Thank you, Brother Hyatt.

00:31:20.839 --> 00:31:23.839
For opening our eyes to Jesus' question,

00:31:23.839 --> 00:31:29.630
what do you want me to do for you?

