a helper to the publishing committee

00:31:34.630 --> 00:31:37.630
of the inspiring subject,

00:31:37.630 --> 00:31:40.630
let Jehovah inspire you.

00:31:40.630 --> 00:31:45.779
Have you ever had an important decision,

00:31:45.779 --> 00:31:47.779
suddenly thrust on you?

00:31:47.779 --> 00:31:49.779
You thought you knew the right thing to do,

00:31:49.779 --> 00:31:51.779
but as soon as you decide,

00:31:51.779 --> 00:31:53.779
you start having second thoughts,

00:31:53.779 --> 00:31:55.779
maybe even regrets.

00:31:55.779 --> 00:31:57.779
And now you can't stop thinking,

00:31:57.779 --> 00:32:00.779
did I do the right thing?

00:32:00.779 --> 00:32:04.779
This tendency to repeat a thought over and over again

00:32:04.779 --> 00:32:06.779
is called rumination.

00:32:06.779 --> 00:32:09.779
And when those thoughts make us feel anxious,

00:32:09.779 --> 00:32:12.779
it can be bad for our health.

00:32:12.779 --> 00:32:14.779
Some of you students made tough decisions

00:32:14.779 --> 00:32:16.779
before you came to this class.

00:32:16.779 --> 00:32:18.779
Thank you for that.

00:32:18.779 --> 00:32:21.779
And everyone right now is faced with challenging decisions

00:32:21.779 --> 00:32:23.779
every day.

00:32:23.779 --> 00:32:29.779
So what can we do to stop anxious rumination once it starts?

00:32:29.779 --> 00:32:33.779
Well, open your Bibles with me to Psalm 37 verse 5,

00:32:33.779 --> 00:32:36.779
and notice the advice that is given to us here.

00:32:36.779 --> 00:32:41.700
Commit your way to Jehovah,

00:32:41.700 --> 00:32:43.700
rely on him,

00:32:43.700 --> 00:32:47.700
and he will act in your behalf.

00:32:47.700 --> 00:32:50.700
Now the word for commit here literally means

00:32:50.700 --> 00:32:53.700
to roll or remove something from our life.

00:32:53.700 --> 00:32:55.700
So as the footnote says,

00:32:55.700 --> 00:32:57.700
we need to roll our way,

00:32:57.700 --> 00:33:01.700
our concerns, our anxieties upon Jehovah.

00:33:01.700 --> 00:33:04.700
When we ruminate anxiously,

00:33:04.700 --> 00:33:07.700
we're holding on to our problem.

00:33:07.700 --> 00:33:10.700
But the Bible says through prayer,

00:33:10.700 --> 00:33:13.700
we have to take the problem off our shoulders

00:33:13.700 --> 00:33:15.700
and put it on Jehovah's.

00:33:15.700 --> 00:33:19.700
In other words, we no longer act as if the burden is ours.

00:33:19.700 --> 00:33:23.700
We need to leave it in his hands.

00:33:23.700 --> 00:33:25.700
It sounds so simple,

00:33:25.700 --> 00:33:27.700
but at times it's hard to do.

00:33:27.700 --> 00:33:32.700
So what can help us when we have trouble letting go?

00:33:32.700 --> 00:33:34.700
Well, our suggestion today

00:33:34.700 --> 00:33:39.700
is to let Jehovah inspire you with awe.

00:33:39.700 --> 00:33:41.700
Now to inspire someone

00:33:41.700 --> 00:33:45.700
means to make them feel that they want to do something

00:33:45.700 --> 00:33:46.700
and can do it.

00:33:46.700 --> 00:33:49.700
And it may be that Jehovah gave us the emotion of awe

00:33:49.700 --> 00:33:52.700
for that very purpose.

00:33:52.700 --> 00:33:54.700
You may be wondering now,

00:33:54.700 --> 00:33:56.700
how can awe help me?

