Notice,

00:34:15.699 --> 00:34:18.699
Jacob departed from Beersheba

00:34:18.699 --> 00:34:21.699
and kept going toward Herod.

00:34:21.699 --> 00:34:24.699
Why was he going there?

00:34:24.699 --> 00:34:27.699
Well, the main reason was to get away from his brother Issa.

00:34:27.699 --> 00:34:28.699
Why?

00:34:28.699 --> 00:34:31.699
Because Jacob had just made a tough decision

00:34:31.699 --> 00:34:34.699
and Issa was mad.

00:34:34.699 --> 00:34:36.699
You know the story.

00:34:36.699 --> 00:34:38.699
For most of his life,

00:34:38.699 --> 00:34:41.699
Issa despised the family birthright.

00:34:41.699 --> 00:34:43.699
And that upset Jacob very much.

00:34:43.699 --> 00:34:45.699
So at some point,

00:34:45.699 --> 00:34:48.699
he purchased the birthright from him.

00:34:48.699 --> 00:34:49.699
Years go by.

00:34:49.699 --> 00:34:51.699
And then one day,

00:34:51.699 --> 00:34:54.699
their father Isaac is getting ready to bless Issa

00:34:54.699 --> 00:34:56.699
as the firstborn.

