It's not possible today to know all the factors

00:35:05.699 --> 00:35:08.699
that influenced Isaac, Rebecca, and Jacob back then.

00:35:08.699 --> 00:35:10.699
But the fact is,

00:35:10.699 --> 00:35:14.699
Jacob's decision put a strain on the whole family.

00:35:14.699 --> 00:35:18.699
Issa began plotting to kill his brother.

00:35:18.699 --> 00:35:22.699
And that's why Jacob was on the road.

00:35:22.699 --> 00:35:24.699
Do you think he might have been

00:35:24.699 --> 00:35:27.699
ruminating a bit that day on what happened?

00:35:27.699 --> 00:35:30.699
Did he perhaps have second thoughts?

00:35:30.699 --> 00:35:32.699
Was he asking himself,

00:35:32.699 --> 00:35:34.699
did I do the right thing?

00:35:34.699 --> 00:35:37.699
Was it okay to fool my father?

00:35:37.699 --> 00:35:40.699
What does Jehovah think of me now?

00:35:40.699 --> 00:35:43.699
Those would have been reasonable questions.

00:35:43.699 --> 00:35:46.699
Of course, we don't know what Jacob was thinking.

00:35:46.699 --> 00:35:49.699
But if he was having second thoughts,

00:35:49.699 --> 00:35:51.699
what happened next

00:35:51.699 --> 00:35:54.699
must have helped him to stop ruminating on them.

00:35:54.699 --> 00:35:58.699
Notice what we read in verses 11 and 12.

00:35:58.699 --> 00:36:00.699
In time,

00:36:00.699 --> 00:36:02.699
he came to a place

00:36:02.699 --> 00:36:04.699
and prepared to spend the night there

00:36:04.699 --> 00:36:06.699
because the sun had set.

